26/09/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- A two-day meeting of the army chiefs of the Adriatic Charter signatories -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- was due to begin in Ohrid on Monday (26 September). 
In addition to the three top military commanders -- Albania's General Pellumb Qazimi, Croatia's Josip Lucic and Macedonia's Miroslav Stojanovski -- their counterparts from Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria and Serbia-Montenegro are scheduled to attend, as are senior US and NATO representatives. 
Ahead of the event, the defence ministers of Albania and Macedonia met in Ohrid on Sunday and agreed to further boost bilateral co-operation in the defence sector. 
(Telma TV, RTS, Makfax - 26/09/05; A1 TV - 25/09/05)
